properties.name: oncached
properties.description: The resources listed in the manifest have been downloaded, and the application is now cached.

properties.name: onchecking
properties.description: The user agent is checking for an update, or attempting to download the manifest for the first time. This is always the first event in the sequence.

properties.name: ondownloading
properties.description: The user agent has found an update and is fetching it, or is downloading the resources listed by the manifest for the first time.

properties.name: onerror
properties.description: Indicates an error has occurred.

properties.name: onnoupdate
properties.description: Indicates the manifest has not changed.

properties.name: onobsolete
properties.description: The Webpage is associated with an application cache whose group is marked as obsolete.

properties.name: onprogress
properties.description: The user agent is downloading resources listed by the manifest. The event object's total attribute returns the total number of files to be downloaded. The event object's loaded attribute returns the number of files processed so far.

properties.name: onupdateready
properties.description: The ApplicationCache object's cache host is associated with an application cache whose application cache group's update status is idle, and whose application cache group is not marked as obsolete, but that application cache is not the newest cache in its group.

properties.name: status
properties.description: Returns the current status of the application cache, as given by the constants defined below.

properties.name: enabled
properties.description: Returns true if the given track is active, and false otherwise. Can be set, to change whether the track is enabled or not. If multiple audio tracks are enabled simultaneously, they are mixed.

properties.name: id
properties.description: Returns the ID of the given track. This is the ID that can be used with a fragment identifier if the format supports the Media Fragments URI syntax, and that can be used with the getTrackById() method.

properties.name: kind
properties.description: Returns the category the given track falls into.

properties.name: label
properties.description: Returns the label of the given track, if known, or the empty string otherwise.

properties.name: language
properties.description: Returns the language of the given track, if known, or the empty string otherwise.

properties.name: length
properties.description: Returns the number of tracks in the list.

properties.name: activeCues
properties.description: Returns the text track cues from the text track list of cues that are currently active (i.e. that start before the current playback position and end after it), as a TextTrackCueList object.

properties.name: cues
properties.description: Returns the text track list of cues, as a TextTrackCueList object.

properties.name: inBandMetadataTrackDispatchType
properties.description: Returns the text track in-band metadata track dispatch type string.

properties.name: kind
properties.description: Returns the text track kind string.

properties.name: label
properties.description: Returns the text track label, if there is one, or the empty string otherwise (indicating that a custom label probably needs to be generated from the other attributes of the object if the object is exposed to the user).

properties.name: language
properties.description: Returns the text track language string.

properties.name: mode
properties.description: The text track mode, represented by a string from the following list. "disabled": The text track disabled mode. "hidden": The text track hidden mode. "showing": The text track showing mode.

properties.name: align
properties.description: A string representing the text track cue alignment, as follows. If it is start alignment: the string "start". If it is middle alignment: the string "middle". If it is end alignment: the string "end". If it is left alignment: the string "left". If it is right alignment: the string "right".

properties.name: endTime
properties.description: The text track cue end time, in seconds.

properties.name: id
properties.description: The text track cue identifier.

properties.name: line
properties.description: The text track cue line position. In the case of the value being auto, the string "auto" is returned.

properties.name: pauseOnExit
properties.description: The text track cue pause-on-exit flag.

properties.name: position
properties.description: The text track cue text position.

properties.name: size
properties.description: The text track cue size.

properties.name: snapToLines
properties.description: The text track cue snap-to-lines flag.

properties.name: startTime
properties.description: The text track cue start time, in seconds.

properties.name: text
properties.description: The text track cue text in raw unparsed form.

properties.name: track
properties.description: Returns the TextTrack object to which this text track cue belongs, if any, or null otherwise.

properties.name: vertical
properties.description: A string representing the text track cue writing direction, as follows. If it is horizontal: The empty string. If it is vertical growing left: The string "rl". If it is vertical growing right: The string "lr".

properties.name: length
properties.description: The length attribute returns the number of cues in the list represented by the TextTrackCueList.

properties.name: length
properties.description: The length attribute of a TextTrackList object returns the number of text tracks in the list represented by the TextTrackList.

properties.name: length
properties.description: Returns the number of ranges in the object.

properties.name: track
properties.description: Returns the track object (TextTrack, AudioTrack, or VideoTrack) to which the event relates.

properties.name: html/elements/canvas
properties.description: A (read-only) reference to the ''canvas'' element that the CanvasRenderingContext2D object was created for.

properties.name: fillStyle
properties.description: The current style used to fill shapes. The style can be a [[apis/canvas/CanvasGradient|CanvasGradient]], a [[apis/canvas/CanvasPattern|CanvasPattern]], or a string containing a CSS color.

properties.name: font
properties.description: The current canvas context font and characteristics, in the manner of the CSS ''font'' property.

properties.name: globalAlpha
properties.description: An alpha value that is applied to shapes and images before they are composited onto the canvas.

properties.name: globalCompositeOperation
properties.description: Sets how shapes and images are drawn onto the existing bitmap once they have had globalAlpha and the current transformation matrix applied.

properties.name: lineCap
properties.description: Defines the type of endings the user agent will place on the end of lines.

properties.name: lineDashOffset
properties.description: Specifies the number of pixels to offset the dash pattern.

properties.name: lineJoin
properties.description: Defines the type of corners the user agent will place where two lines meet.

properties.name: lineWidth
properties.description: The current line width, in coordinate space units.

properties.name: miterLimit
properties.description: The current miter limit ratio.

properties.name: shadowBlur
properties.description: Specifies the level of the blurring effect. The units do not map to coordinate space units, and are not affected by the current transformation matrix.

properties.name: shadowColor
properties.description: The color of the shadow.

properties.name: shadowOffsetX
properties.description: Specifies the distance that the shadow will be offset in the positive horizontal distance, in coordinate space units.

properties.name: shadowOffsetY
properties.description: Specifies the distance that the shadow will be offset in the positive vertical distance, in coordinate space units.

properties.name: strokeStyle
properties.description: The current style for stroking shapes. The style can be a [[apis/canvas/CanvasGradient|CanvasGradient]], a [[apis/canvas/CanvasPattern|CanvasPattern]], or a string containing a CSS color.

properties.name: textAlign
properties.description: Returns or sets the text alignment value. See return value description below.

properties.name: textBaseline
properties.description: Returns or sets the baseline value. See return value description below.

properties.name: data
properties.description: Initialized to a Uint8ClampedArray object. The Uint8ClampedArray object must use a Canvas Pixel ArrayBuffer for its storage, and must have a zero start offset and a length equal to the length of its storage, in bytes.

properties.name: height
properties.description: The number of rows in the image data.

properties.name: width
properties.description: The number of physical device pixels per row in the image data.

properties.name: actualBoundingBoxAscent
properties.description: The distance from the horizontal line indicated by the textBaseline attribute to the top of the bounding rectangle of the given text, in CSS pixels; positive numbers indicating a distance going up from the given baseline.

properties.name: actualBoundingBoxDescent
properties.description: The distance from the horizontal line indicated by the textBaseline attribute to the bottom of the bounding rectangle of the given text, in CSS pixels; positive numbers indicating a distance going down from the given baseline.

properties.name: actualBoundingBoxLeft
properties.description: The distance parallel to the baseline from the alignment point given by the textAlign attribute to the left side of the bounding rectangle of the given text, in CSS pixels; positive numbers indicating a distance going left from the given alignment point.

properties.name: actualBoundingBoxRight
properties.description: The distance parallel to the baseline from the alignment point given by the textAlign attribute to the right side of the bounding rectangle of the given text, in CSS pixels; positive numbers indicating a distance going right from the given alignment point.

properties.name: alphabeticBaseline
properties.description: The distance from the horizontal line indicated by the textBaseline attribute to the alphabetic baseline of the line box, in CSS pixels; positive numbers indicating that the given baseline is below the alphabetic baseline. (Zero if the given baseline is the alphabetic baseline.)

properties.name: emHeightAscent
properties.description: The distance from the horizontal line indicated by the textBaseline attribute to the top of the em square in the line box, in CSS pixels; positive numbers indicating that the given baseline is below the top of the em square (so this value will usually be positive). Zero if the given baseline is the top of the em square; half the font size if the given baseline is the middle of the em square.

properties.name: emHeightDescent
properties.description: The distance from the horizontal line indicated by the textBaseline attribute to the bottom of the em square in the line box, in CSS pixels; positive numbers indicating that the given baseline is below the bottom of the em square (so this value will usually be negative). (Zero if the given baseline is the top of the em square.)

properties.name: fontBoundingBoxAscent
properties.description: The distance from the horizontal line indicated by the textBaseline attribute to the top of the highest bounding rectangle of all the fonts used to render the text, in CSS pixels; positive numbers indicating a distance going up from the given baseline.

properties.name: fontBoundingBoxDescent
properties.description: The distance from the horizontal line indicated by the textBaseline attribute to the bottom of the lowest bounding rectangle of all the fonts used to render the text, in CSS pixels; positive numbers indicating a distance going down from the given baseline.

properties.name: hangingBaseline
properties.description: The distance from the horizontal line indicated by the textBaseline attribute to the hanging baseline of the line box, in CSS pixels; positive numbers indicating that the given baseline is below the hanging baseline. (Zero if the given baseline is the hanging baseline.)

properties.name: ideographicBaseline
properties.description: The distance from the horizontal line indicated by the textBaseline attribute to the ideographic baseline of the line box, in CSS pixels; positive numbers indicating that the given baseline is below the ideographic baseline. (Zero if the given baseline is the ideographic baseline.)

properties.name: width
properties.description: The width of an inline text box, in CSS pixels.

properties.name: firstEmptyRegionIndex
properties.description: Returns the integer index of the first empty element within a region chain. Returns -1 if the content fits within the region chain or if it exceeds available space.

properties.name: name
properties.description: Name of flow, as specified by any element's  [[css/properties/flow-from|'''flow-from''']] or [[css/properties/flow-into|'''flow-into''']] properties.

properties.name: overset
properties.description: Indicates whether a flow's content exceeds available space within a region chain, or if no available region chain in which to flow content exists.

properties.name: regionOverset
properties.description: A region's display state within a region chain.

properties.name: lastModifiedDate
properties.description: The last modified date of the file. On getting, if user agents can make this information available, this must return a new Date object initialized to the last modified date of the file. If the last modification date and time are not known, the attribute must return the current date and time as a Date object.

properties.name: name
properties.description: The name of the file; on getting, this must return the name of the file as a string. There are numerous file name variations on different systems; this is merely the name of the file, without path information. On getting, if user agents cannot make this information available, they must return the empty string.

properties.name: length
properties.description: '''length''' returns the number of files in the FileList object. If there are no files, this attribute must return 0.

properties.name: onabort
properties.description: Indicates that the read has been aborted (for example, by calling '''abort()''').

properties.name: filesystem
properties.description: The file system on which the Entry resides.

properties.name: fullPath
properties.description: The full absolute path from the root to the Entry.

properties.name: isDirectory
properties.description: True if the Entry is a directory.

properties.name: isFile
properties.description: True if the Entry is a file.

properties.name: name
properties.description: The name of the Entry, excluding the path leading to it.

properties.name: filesystem
properties.description: The file system on which the EntrySync resides.

properties.name: fullPath
properties.description: The full absolute path from the root to the EntrySync.

properties.name: isDirectory
properties.description: True if the EntrySync is a directory.

properties.name: isFile
properties.description: True if the EntrySync is a file.

properties.name: name
properties.description: The name of the EntrySync, excluding the path leading to it.

properties.name: name
properties.description: The name of the file system. The specifics of naming filesystems is unspecified, but a name must be unique across the list of exposed file systems.

properties.name: root
properties.description: The root directory of the file system.

properties.name: name
properties.description: The name of the file system. The specifics of naming filesystems is unspecified, but a name must be unique across the list of exposed file systems.

properties.name: root
properties.description: The root directory of the file system.

properties.name: axes
properties.description: Array of values for all axes of the gamepad.

properties.name: buttons
properties.description: Array of values for all buttons of the gamepad.

properties.name: id
properties.description: A string that identifies the brand or style of connected gamepad device.

properties.name: index
properties.description: The index of the gamepad in the '''Navigator'''.

properties.name: timestamp
properties.description: A timestamp indicating the last time the data for this gamepad was updated.

properties.name: gamepad
properties.description: Provides access to the associated gamepad data for this event.

properties.name: accuracy
properties.description: Denotes the accuracy level of the ''latitude'' and ''longitude'' coordinates. It is specified in meters and must be supported by all implementations. The value of this attribute must be a non-negative real number.

properties.name: alititudeAccuracy
properties.description: Denotes the accuracy level of the ''altitude'' coordinate, specified in meters. If the implementation cannot provide altitude information, the value of this attribute must be null.

properties.name: altitude
properties.description: Denotes the height of the position, specified in meters above the ellipsoid. If the implementation cannot provide altitude information, the value of this attribute must be null.

properties.name: heading
properties.description: Denotes the direction of travel of the hosting device specified in degrees, where 0° ≤ heading < 360°, counting clockwise relative to the true north. If the implementation cannot provide heading information, the value of this attribute must be null. If the hosting device is stationary (i.e., the value of the ''speed'' attribute is 0), then the value of this attribute must be NaN.

properties.name: latitude
properties.description: Geographic latitude specified in decimal degrees.

properties.name: longitude
properties.description: Geographic longitude specified in decimal degrees.

properties.name: speed
properties.description: Denotes the magnitude of the horizontal component of the hosting device's current velocity specified in meters per second. If the implementation cannot provide speed information, the value of this attribute must be null. Otherwise, the value of this attribute must be a non-negative real number.

properties.name: coords
properties.description: Contains a set of geographic coordinates together with their associated accuracy, as well as a set of other optional attributes such as altitude and speed.

properties.name: timestamp
properties.description: Represents the time when the Position object was acquired, represented as a ''DOMTimeStamp''.

properties.name: code
properties.description: The error code of the current PositionError.

properties.name: message
properties.description: The error text of the current PositionError, describing the details of the error encountered. This attribute is primarily intended for debugging and developers should not use it directly in their application user interface.

properties.name: enableHighAccuracy
properties.description: A request from the application to receive the best possible results.

properties.name: maximumAge
properties.description: Indicates that the application is willing to accept a cached position whose age is no greater than the specified time (in milliseconds).

properties.name: timeout
properties.description: Denotes the maximum length of time (expressed in milliseconds) that is allowed to pass from the call to '''getCurrentPosition()''' or '''watchPosition()''' until the corresponding '''successCallback''' is invoked.

properties.name: indexedDB
properties.description: Provides access to the IndexedDB features supported by the browser and/or device.

properties.name: direction
properties.description: Indicates the direction of travel within a cursor.

properties.name: key
properties.description: The key value for the record currently displayed by the cursor.

properties.name: primaryKey
properties.description: Returns the cursor's current effective key.

properties.name: source
properties.description: On getting, returns the IDBObjectStore or IDBIndex that the cursor is iterating. This function never returns null or throws an exception, even if the cursor is currently being iterated, has iterated past its end, or its transaction is not active.

properties.name: name
properties.description: Name of the connected database.

properties.name: objectStoreNames
properties.description: Returns a list of names of the object stores currently in the connected database.

properties.name: version
properties.description: Returns the version of the database when this IDBDatabaseSync instance was created.

properties.name: code
properties.description: Not supported.

properties.name: message
properties.description: Not supported.

properties.name: keyPath
properties.description: The key path of this index. If null, this index is not auto-populated.

properties.name: multiEntry
properties.description: Affects how the index behaves when the result of evaluating the index's key path yields an array. If true, there is one record in the index for each item in an array of keys. If false, then there is one record for each key that is an array.

properties.name: name
properties.description: The name of this index.

properties.name: objectStore
properties.description: Returns a reference to the IDBObjectStore instance for the referenced object store in this IDBIndex's transaction.

properties.name: unique
properties.description: Provides the unique flag of this index.

properties.name: lower
properties.description: This value is the lower-bound of the key range.

properties.name: lowerOpen
properties.description: Returns false if the lower-bound value is included in the key range. Returns true if the lower-bound value is excluded from the key range.

properties.name: upperOpen
properties.description: Returns false if the upper-bound value is included in the key range. Returns true if the upper-bound value is excluded from the key range.

properties.name: autoIncrement
properties.description: Provides the auto increment flag for this object store.

properties.name: indexNames
properties.description: Provides a list of the names of indexes on objects in this object store.

properties.name: keyPath
properties.description: Provides the key path of this object store.

properties.name: name
properties.description: Provides the name of this object store.

properties.name: transaction
properties.description: Returns the transaction this object store belongs to.

properties.name: onUpgradeNeeded
properties.description: The event handler for the upgrade needed event.

properties.name: onblocked
properties.description: The event handler for the blocked event. This event is triggered when the upgradeneeded should be triggered because of a version change but the database is still in use (ie not closed) somewhere, even after the versionchange event was sent.

properties.name: error
properties.description: The error codes returned under certain conditions.

properties.name: onerror
properties.description: The event handler for the error event.

properties.name: onsuccess
properties.description: The event handler for the success event.

properties.name: readyState
properties.description: The state of the request. Every request starts in the pending state. The state changes to done when the request completes successfully or when an error occurs.

properties.name: result
properties.description: Returns the result of the request. If the the request failed and the result is not available, the DOMException InvalidStateError exception is thrown.

properties.name: source
properties.description: The source of the request, such as an Index or a ObjectStore. If no source exists (such as when calling indexedDB.open()), it returns null.

properties.name: transaction
properties.description: The transaction for the request. This property can be null for certain requests, such as for request returned from IDBFactory.open (You're just connecting to a database, so there is no transaction to return).

properties.name: db
properties.description: The database connection of which this transaction is a part.

properties.name: error
properties.description: Null if the transaction is not finished, is finished and successfully committed, or was aborted with the abort() function. Returns the same DOMError as the request object which caused the transaction to be aborted due to a failed request, or a DOMError for the transaction failure not due to a failed request (such as QuotaExceededError or UnknownError).

properties.name: mode
properties.description: The mode for isolating access to data in the object stores that are in the scope of the transaction. For possible values, see Return Value, below. The default value is readonly.

properties.name: onabort
properties.description: The event handler for the onabort event.

properties.name: oncomplete
properties.description: The event handler for the oncomplete event.

properties.name: onerror
properties.description: The event handler for the error event.

properties.name: newVersion
properties.description: Returns the new version of the database, which is the version specified by the open request.

properties.name: oldVersion
properties.description: Returns the old version of the database.

properties.name: onblocked
properties.description: The event handler for the blocked event.

properties.name: hash
properties.description: The hash property contains the fragment identifier (including hash character) for the current page.

properties.name: host
properties.description: The host property contains the host part of the the current document URL, (hostname:port).

properties.name: hostname
properties.description: The hostname property contains the hostname the current document was served from, excluding protocol, port, and other information.

properties.name: href
properties.description: The full url for this resource. Synonymous with String(window.location).

properties.name: pathname
properties.description: The path to the current document, relative to the root of the current host.

properties.name: port
properties.description: The port number the document was accessed via.

properties.name: protocol
properties.description:
Sets or retrieves the protocol portion of a URL.
The protocol the current document was accessed via (everything preceding the "//").

properties.name: search
properties.description: The search property contains the query string portion of the current url.

properties.name: navigation
properties.description: This attribute is defined by the '''PerformanceNavigation''' interface.

properties.name: timing
properties.description: Represents the timing information related to the browsing contexts since the last non-redirect navigation. This attribute is defined by the '''PerformanceTiming''' interface.

properties.name: redirectCount
properties.description: Returns the number of redirects since the last non-redirect navigation under the current browsing context. If there is no redirect or there is any redirect that is not from the same origin as the destination document, returns zero.

properties.name: type
properties.description: Returns the type of the last non-redirect navigation in the current browsing context. See Notes.

properties.name: connectEnd
properties.description: Returns the time immediately after the user agent finishes establishing the connection to the server to retrieve the current document.

properties.name: connectStart
properties.description: Returns the time immediately before the user agent start establishing the connection to the server to retrieve the document.

properties.name: domComplete
properties.description: Returns the time immediately before the user agent sets the current document readiness to "complete".

properties.name: domContentLoadedEventStart
properties.description: Returns the time immediately before the user agent fires the DOMContentLoaded event at the Document.

properties.name: domInteractive
properties.description: Returns the time immediately before the user agent sets the current document readiness to "interactive".

properties.name: domLoading
properties.description: Returns the time immediately before the user agent sets the current document readiness to "loading".

properties.name: domainLookupEnd
properties.description: Returns the time immediately after the user agent finishes the domain name lookup for the current document.

properties.name: domainLookupStart
properties.description: Returns the time immediately before the user agent starts the domain name lookup for the current document.

properties.name: fetchStart
properties.description: Returns the time immediately before the user agent starts checking any relevant application caches (if the resource is to be fetched using HTTP GET or equivalent). Otherwise, returns the time when the user agent starts fetching the resource.

properties.name: loadEventEnd
properties.description: Returns the time when the load event of the current document is completed, or returns zero when the load event is not fired or is not completed.

properties.name: loadEventStart
properties.description: Returns the time immediately before the load event of the current document is fired, or returns zero when the load event is not fired yet.

properties.name: navigationStart
properties.description: Returns the time immediately after the user agent finishes prompting to unload the previous document. If there is no previous document, returns the same value as fetchStart.

properties.name: redirectEnd
properties.description: Returns the time immediately after receiving the last byte of the response of the last redirect, if there are HTTP redirects or equivalent when navigating and all redirects and equivalents are from the same origin. Otherwise, returns zero.

properties.name: redirectStart
properties.description: Returns the starting time of the fetch that initiates the redirect, if there are HTTP redirects or equivalent when navigating and if all the redirects or equivalent are from the same origin,. Otherwise, returns zero.

properties.name: requestStart
properties.description: Returns the time immediately before the user agent starts requesting the current document from the server, or from relevant application caches or from local resources. If the transport connection fails after a request is sent and the user agent reopens a connection and resends the request, returns the corresponding values of the new request.

properties.name: responseEnd
properties.description: Returns the time immediately after the user agent receives the last byte of the current document from the server, relevant application caches or from local resources, or immediately before the transport connection is closed, whichever comes first.

properties.name: responseStart
properties.description: Returns the time immediately after the user agent receives the first byte of the response from the server, or from relevant application caches or from local resources.

properties.name: secureConnectionStart
properties.description: Returns the time immediately before the user agent starts the handshake process to secure the current connection, if the scheme of the current page is HTTPS. If HTTPS is not used, returns zero.

properties.name: unloadEventEnd
properties.description: Returns the time immediately after the user agent finishes the unload event of the previous document. If there is no previous document or the previous document has a different origin than the current document or the unload is not yet completed, returns zero.

properties.name: unloadEventStart
properties.description: Returns the time immediately before the user agent starts the unload event of the previous document. If there is no previous document or the previous document has a different origin than the current document, returns zero.

properties.name: onresourcetimingbufferfull
properties.description: This callback is triggered when the buffer used to store the list of PerformanceResourceTiming is full.

properties.name: connectEnd
properties.description: Returns the time immediately after the user agent finishes establishing the connection to the server to retrieve the resource.

properties.name: connectStart
properties.description: Returns the time immediately before the user agent starts establishing the connection to the server to retrieve the resource.

properties.name: domainLookupEnd
properties.description: Returns the time immediately after the user agent finishes the domain name lookup for the resource.

properties.name: domainLookupStart
properties.description: Returns the time immediately before the user agent starts the domain name lookup for the resource.

properties.name: fetchStart
properties.description: Returns the time immediately before the user agent starts to fetch the resource.

properties.name: initiatorType
properties.description: Returns a DOMString representing the type of object that initiated the request for the resource. See Return Value.

properties.name: redirectEnd
properties.description: Returns the time immediately after receiving the last byte of the response of the last redirect.

properties.name: redirectStart
properties.description: Returns the starting time of the fetch that initiates the redirect.

properties.name: requestStart
properties.description: Returns the time immediately before the user agent starts requesting the resource from the server, or from relevant application caches or from local resources.

properties.name: responseEnd
properties.description: Returns the time immediately after the user agent finishes receiving the last byte of the resource from from relevant application caches or from local resources.

properties.name: responseStart
properties.description: Returns the time immediately after the user agent receives the first byte of the response from the server, or from relevant application caches or from local resources.

properties.name: secureConnectionStart
properties.description: Returns the time immediately before the user agent starts the handshake process to secure the current connection.

properties.name: domContentLoadedEventEnd
properties.description: Returns the time immediately after the document's DOMContentLoaded event completes.

properties.name: port2

properties.name: localStorage
properties.description: Provides a Storage object for an origin.

properties.name: sessionStorage
properties.description: Provides a Storage object specific to the current top-level browsing context.

properties.description: The size of the FFT used for frequency-domain analysis. This must be a power of two.

properties.name: frequencyBinCount
properties.description: Half the [[apis/webaudio/AnalyserNode/fftSize|'''fftSize''']] (the size of the FFT used for frequency-domain analysis).

properties.name: maxDecibels
properties.description: The maximum power value in the scaling range for the FFT analysis data for conversion to unsigned byte values.

properties.name: minDecibels
properties.description: The minimum power value in the scaling range for the FFT analysis data for conversion to unsigned byte values.

properties.name: smoothingTimeConstant
properties.description: A value from 0 to 1 where 0 represents no time averaging with the last analysis frame.

properties.description: Duration of the PCM audio data in seconds.

properties.name: numberOfChannels

properties.name: sampleRate
properties.description: The sample-rate for the PCM audio data in samples per second.

properties.name: buffer
properties.description: Represents the audio asset to be played.

properties.name: loop
properties.description: Indicates if the audio data should play in a loop. The default value is false.

properties.name: loopEnd
properties.description: An optional value in seconds where looping should end if the loop attribute is true. Its default value is 0, and it may usefully be set to any value between 0 and the duration of the buffer.

properties.name: loopStart
properties.description: An optional value in seconds where looping should begin if the loop attribute is true. Its default value is 0, and it may usefully be set to any value between 0 and the duration of the buffer.

properties.name: playbackRate
properties.description: The speed at which to render the audio stream. The default [[apis/webaudio/AudioBufferSourceNode/playbackRate|'''playbackRate''']] value is 1. This parameter is a-rate.

properties.name: playbackState
properties.description: The playback state, initialized to UNSCHEDULED_STATE, progressing through SCHEDULED_STATE, PLAYING_STATE, and FINISHED_STATE.

properties.name: activeSourceCount
properties.description: The number of [[apis/webaudio/AudioBufferSourceNode|'''AudioBufferSourceNode''']]s that are currently playing.

properties.name: currentTime
properties.description: This is a time in seconds which starts at zero when the context is created and increases in real-time. All scheduled times are relative to it. This is not a ''transport'' time which can be started, paused, and re-positioned. It is always moving forward. A GarageBand-like timeline transport system can be very easily built on top of this (in JavaScript). This time corresponds to an ever-increasing hardware timestamp.

properties.name: destination
properties.description: An [[apis/webaudio/AudioDestinationNode|'''AudioDestinationNode''']] with a single input representing the final destination for all audio (to be rendered to the audio hardware). All [[apis/webaudio/AudioNode|'''AudioNode''']]s actively rendering audio will directly or indirectly connect to destination.

properties.name: listener
properties.description: An [[apis/webaudio/AudioListener|'''AudioListener''']] which is used for 3D spatialization.

properties.name: sampleRate
properties.description: The sample rate (in sample-frames per second) at which the [[apis/webaudio/AudioContext|'''AudioContext''']] handles audio. It is assumed that all [[apis/webaudio/AudioNode|'''AudioNode''']]s in the context run at this rate. In making this assumption, sample-rate converters or ''varispeed'' processors are not supported in real-time processing.

properties.name: maxNumberOfChannels
properties.description: The maximum number of channels that the [[apis/webaudio/AudioDestinationNode/numberOfChannels|'''numberOfChannels''']] attribute can be set to; that is, the maximum number of channels that this hardware is capable of supporting. A value of 0 indicates that [[apis/webaudio/AudioDestinationNode/maxNumberOfChannels|'''maxNumberOfChannels''']] may not be changed. This will be the case for an [[apis/webaudio/AudioDestinationNode|'''AudioDestinationNode''']] in an [[apis/webaudio/OfflineAudioContext|'''OfflineAudioContext''']].

properties.name: numberOfChannels
properties.description: The number of channels of the destination's input. This value will default to 2, and may be set to any non-zero value less than or equal to [[apis/webaudio/AudioDestinationNode/maxNumberOfChannels|'''maxNumberOfChannels''']]. An exception will be thrown if this value is not within the valid range.

properties.name: dopplerFactor
properties.description: A constant used to determine the amount of pitch shift to use when rendering a doppler effect. The default value is 1.

properties.name: speedOfSound
properties.description: The speed of sound used for calculating doppler shift. The default value is 343.3 meters / second.

properties.name: context
properties.description: The [[apis/webaudio/AudioContext|'''AudioContext''']] that owns this [[apis/webaudio/AudioNode|'''AudioNode''']].

properties.name: numberOfInputs
properties.description: The number of inputs feeding into the [[apis/webaudio/AudioNode|'''AudioNode''']]. This will be 0 for an [[apis/webaudio/AudioSourceNode|'''AudioSourceNode''']].

properties.name: numberOfOutputs
properties.description: The number of outputs coming out of the [[apis/webaudio/AudioNode|'''AudioNode''']]. This will be 0 for an [[apis/webaudio/AudioDestinationNode|'''AudioDestinationNode''']].

properties.name: computedValue
properties.description: The final value controlling the audio DSP, calculated at each time, which is either the value set directly to the value attribute or, if there are any scheduled parameter changes (automation events), the value as calculated from these events.

properties.name: defaultValue
properties.description: Initial value for the value attribute.

properties.name: maxValue
properties.description: Nominal maximum value. The value attribute may be set higher than this value.

properties.name: minValue
properties.description: Nominal minimum value. The value attribute may be set lower than this value.

properties.name: value
properties.description: The parameter's floating-point value. If a value is set outside the allowable range described by [[apis/webaudio/AudioParam/minValue|'''minValue''']] and [[apis/webaudio/AudioParam/maxValue|'''maxValue''']] no exception is thrown, because these limits are just nominal and may be exceeded. If a value is set during a time when there are any automation events scheduled then it will be ignored and no exception will be thrown.

properties.name: inputBuffer
properties.description: An [[apis/webaudio/AudioBuffer|'''AudioBuffer''']] containing the input audio data. It will have a number of channels equal to the '''numberOfInputChannels''' parameter of the [[apis/webaudio/AudioContext/createScriptProcessor|'''createScriptProcessor()''']] method. This [[apis/webaudio/AudioBuffer|'''AudioBuffer''']] is only valid while in the scope of the [[apis/webaudio/ScriptProcessorNode/onaudioprocess|'''onaudioprocess''']] function. Its values will be meaningless outside of this scope.

properties.name: node
properties.description: The [[apis/webaudio/ScriptProcessorNode|'''ScriptProcessorNode''']] associated with this processing event.

properties.name: outputBuffer
properties.description: An [[apis/webaudio/AudioBuffer|'''AudioBuffer''']] where the output audio data should be written. It will have a number of channels equal to the '''numberOfOutputChannels''' parameter of the [[apis/webaudio/AudioContext/createScriptProcessor|'''createScriptProcessor()''']] method. Script code within the scope of the [[apis/webaudio/ScriptProcessorNode/onaudioprocess|'''onaudioprocess''']] function is expected to modify the '''Float32Array''' arrays representing channel data in this [[apis/webaudio/AudioBuffer|'''AudioBuffer''']]. Any script modifications to this [[apis/webaudio/AudioBuffer|'''AudioBuffer''']] outside of this scope will not produce any audible effects.

properties.name: playbackTime
properties.description: The time when the audio will be played, in the same time coordinate system as [[apis/webaudio/AudioContext/currentTime|'''AudioContext.currentTime''']]. [[apis/webaudio/AudioProcessingEvent/playbackTime|'''playbackTime''']] allows for very tight synchronization between processing directly in JavaScript with the other events in the context's rendering graph.

properties.name: Q
properties.description: Used in different ways by the various types. Defaults to 1, with a nominal range of 0.0001 to 1000. This parameter is k-rate.

properties.name: frequency
properties.description: Used in different ways by the various types. Defaults to 350Hz, with a nominal range of 10 to the Nyquist frequency (half the sample-rate). This parameter is k-rate.

properties.name: gain
properties.description: Used in different ways by the various types. Defaults to 0, with a nominal range of -40 to 40. This parameter is k-rate.

properties.name: type
properties.description: The type of [[apis/webaudio/BiquadFilterNode|'''BiquadFilterNode''']].

properties.name: buffer
properties.description: A mono, stereo, or 4-channel [[apis/webaudio/AudioBuffer|'''AudioBuffer''']] containing the (possibly multi-channel) impulse response used by the [[apis/webaudio/ConvolverNode|'''ConvolverNode''']]. At the time when this attribute is set, the buffer and the state of the normalize attribute will be used to configure the [[apis/webaudio/ConvolverNode|'''ConvolverNode''']] with this impulse response having the given normalization.

properties.name: normalize
properties.description: Controls whether the impulse response from the buffer will be scaled by an equal-power normalization when the buffer atttribute is set. Its default value is true in order to achieve a more uniform output level from the convolver when loaded with diverse impulse responses. If normalize is set to false, then the convolution will be rendered with no pre-processing/scaling of the impulse response. Changes to this value do not take effect until the next time the buffer attribute is set. If the normalize attribute is false when the buffer attribute is set then the [[apis/webaudio/ConvolverNode|'''ConvolverNode''']] will perform a linear convolution given the exact impulse response contained within the buffer.

properties.name: delayTime
properties.description: An [[apis/webaudio/AudioParam|'''AudioParam''']] object representing the amount of delay (in seconds) to apply. The default value (delayTime.value) is 0 (no delay). The minimum value is 0 and the maximum value is determined by the '''maxDelayTime''' argument to the [[apis/webaudio/AudioContext|'''AudioContext''']] method [[apis/webaudio/AudioContext/createDelay|'''createDelay''']]. This parameter is k-rate.

properties.name: attack
properties.description: The amount of time (in seconds) to reduce the gain by 10dB. Its default value is 0.003, with a nominal range of 0 to 1. This parameter is k-rate.

properties.name: knee
properties.description: A decibel value representing the range above the threshold where the curve smoothly transitions to the ''ratio'' portion. Its default value is 30, with a nominal range of 0 to 40. This parameter is k-rate.

properties.name: ratio
properties.description: The amount of dB change in input for a 1 dB change in output. Its default value is 12, with a nominal range of 1 to 20. This parameter is k-rate.

properties.name: reduction
properties.description: A read-only decibel value for metering purposes, representing the current amount of gain reduction that the compressor is applying to the signal. If fed no signal the value will be 0 (no gain reduction). The nominal range is -20 to 0. This parameter is k-rate.

properties.name: release
properties.description: The amount of time (in seconds) to increase the gain by 10dB. Its default value is 0.250, with a nominal range of 0 to 1. This parameter is k-rate.

properties.name: threshold
properties.description: The decibel value above which the compression will start taking effect. Its default value is -24, with a nominal range of -100 to 0. This parameter is k-rate.

properties.name: gain
properties.description: Represents the amount of gain to apply. Its default value is 1 (no gain change). The nominal [[apis/webaudio/AudioParam/minValue|'''minValue''']] is 0, but may be set negative for phase inversion. The nominal [[apis/webaudio/AudioParam/maxValue|'''maxValue''']] is 1, but higher values are allowed (no exception thrown). This parameter is a-rate.

properties.name: detune
properties.description: A detuning value (in Cents) which will offset the frequency by the given amount. This parameter is a-rate.

properties.name: frequency
properties.description: The frequency (in Hertz) of the periodic waveform. This parameter is a-rate.

properties.name: playbackState
properties.description: The playback state, initialized to UNSCHEDULED_STATE, progressing through SCHEDULED_STATE, PLAYING_STATE, and FINISHED_STATE.

properties.name: type
properties.description: The shape of the periodic waveform. It may directly be set to any of the type constant values except for CUSTOM. The [[apis/webaudio/OscillatorNode/setWaveTable|'''setWaveTable()''']] method can be used to set a custom waveform, which results in this attribute being set to CUSTOM.

properties.name: coneInnerAngle
properties.description: A parameter for directional audio sources, this is an angle inside of which there will be no volume reduction. The default value is 360.

properties.name: coneOuterAngle
properties.description: A parameter for directional audio sources, this is an angle outside of which the volume will be reduced to a constant value of [[apis/webaudio/PannerNode/coneOuterGain|'''coneOuterGain''']]. The default value is 360.

properties.name: coneOuterGain
properties.description: A parameter for directional audio sources, this is the amount of volume reduction outside of the [[apis/webaudio/PannerNode/coneOuterAngle|'''coneOuterAngle''']]. The default value is 0.

properties.name: distanceModel
properties.description: Determines which algorithm will be used to reduce the volume of an audio source as it moves away from the listener. See below for the available choices. The default is INVERSE_DISTANCE.

properties.name: maxDistance
properties.description: The maximum distance between source and listener, after which the volume will not be reduced any further. The default value is 10000.

properties.name: panningModel
properties.description: Determines which spatialization algorithm will be used to position the audio in 3D space. See below for the available choices. The default is HRTF.

properties.name: refDistance
properties.description: A reference distance for reducing volume as source moves further from the listener. The default value is 1.

properties.name: rolloffFactor
properties.description: Describes how quickly the volume is reduced as source moves away from listener. The default value is 1.

properties.name: bufferSize
properties.description: The size of the buffer (in sample-frames) which needs to be processed each time [[apis/webaudio/ScriptProcessorNode/onaudioprocess|'''onaudioprocess''']] is called. Legal values are 256, 512, 1024, 2048, 4096, 8192, and 16384.

properties.name: onaudioprocess
properties.description: An event listener which is called periodically for audio processing. An event of type [[apis/webaudio/AudioProcessingEvent|'''AudioProcessingEvent''']] will be passed to the event handler.

properties.name: curve
properties.description: The shaping curve used for the waveshaping effect. The input signal is nominally within the range -1 -> +1. Each input sample within this range will index into the shaping curve with a signal level of zero corresponding to the center value of the curve array. Any sample value less than -1 will correspond to the first value in the curve array. Any sample value less greater than +1 will correspond to the last value in the curve array.
